OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1771812211
OL,3,CEvidence around unsolved murder of
OL,4,CGlasgow man Alexander Blue under review
OL,6,FA review of the evidence in the 23-
OL,7,Fyear-old unsolved murder of a Glasgow
OL,8,Fbusinessman is taking place, as the
OL,9,Fvictim's brother says it is an
OL,10,F"absolute disgrace" that to this day
OL,11,Fno-one has been charged over the crime.
OL,13,FAlexander Blue was found badly beaten
OL,14,Foutside his home in Glasgow's west end
OL,15,Fin June 2002.
OL,17,FThe 41-year-old, who ran a company
OL,18,Fcalled the Taxi Centre, died in
OL,19,Fhospital two days later from massive
OL,20,Fhead injuries.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1771812211
OL,3,CEvidence around unsolved murder of
OL,4,CGlasgow man Alexander Blue under review
OL,6,FA neighbour had found him injured on
OL,7,Fthe driveway of his home on Dundonald
OL,8,FRoad in the upmarket Dowanhill area.
OL,10,FDespite repeated police appeals, no
OL,11,Fone has been charged over the murder
OL,12,Fand the case remains unresolved after
OL,13,Ftwo decades.
OL,15,FAlexander's older brother Billy Blue
OL,16,Fhas been seeking justice for years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1771812211
OL,3,CEvidence around unsolved murder of
OL,4,CGlasgow man Alexander Blue under review
OL,6,FWith the 25-year-anniversary of
OL,7,FAlexander's death approaching in June
OL,8,Fnext year, he said the police and
OL,9,FCrown Office should "hang their heads
OL,10,Fin shame" if no one is charged by that
OL,11,Fpoint.
OL,13,FHe told the Press Association he felt
OL,14,Fthe family had been "brushed off" by
OL,15,Fpolice and the legal system, saying:
OL,16,F"How bad does it have to get before
OL,17,Fyou get an outside force in?
OL,19,F"You have to get justice, you can't
OL,20,Flet people kill people and just get
OL,21,Faway with it."
OL,26,@qD@UOUrD@IO]vD@UOUvD@aO]xD@AOU{D@AOU}D@
OL,26,ANO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1771812211
OL,3,CEvidence around unsolved murder of
OL,4,CGlasgow man Alexander Blue under review
OL,6,FAlexander's brother believes there is
OL,7,Fenough evidence to identify the
OL,8,Fculprit behind his brother's death,
OL,9,Fsaying it was "no ordinary murder".
OL,11,FBilly, from Glasgow, said: "It's been
OL,12,Fknown for a considerable length of
OL,13,Ftime who's responsible for Alec's
OL,14,Fmurder.
OL,16,F"I would like to see them brought to
OL,17,Fjustice, it would be a vindication."
OL,19,FHe said the Crown Office was
OL,20,F"definitely" reviewing evidence around
OL,21,Fthe case.
OL,26,@qD@OOUqD@bO]sD@\OUxD@AOUyD@dO]|D@AOU|D@
OL,26,ALO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
